dialogueContent.words: We're expecting the {TEAM_TAR.FactionDef.Demonym} forces to begin their assault on this facility at any moment. If they destroy it, our employers lose their eyes on the operational area; they'll scrub the mission at that point.

So here's the plan. We're going to hold the {TEAM_TAR.FactionDef.Demonym} force and keep them busy, and well away from the friendly facility. Meanwhile, a {TEAM_HOST.FactionDef.Demonym} strike force will be inbound to the AO.

Once they land, they'll engage everyone -- friendly and hostile -- and generally stir up trouble. The goal is to get them to take the brunt of the enemy fire; we move in and clean up the mess afterwards.
The number one priority is to destroy that base. Once it's gone, the {TEAM_TAR.FactionDef.Demonym} brass will call off the assault, and we'll be clear to evac. Questions?
Yeah, whose bullshit idea was this, anyway?
Not helpful, Meyer. Stay on station to make the pickup once the base is down. Commander... good luck.
Oh thank God. Commander, that's the friendly reinforcements. We can leave whenever you're ready.
I'll pick you up at the designated LZ.
This was always going to be a long shot. Let's get clear of this, Commander.
Boss, I'm seeing turrets powering up. Big ones. Holy shit.
Commander, I'm seeing hostile defenders surrounding the enemy base.
We can't complete the contract until those units are destroyed.
The opfor's holding forces back at the captured base, presumably to cover their intel teams. They're optional targets, Commander.
Good kill, Commander.
The friendly facility is under fire, Commander. If we lose it, the mission is scrubbed.
Hey, guys? What was that flash I just saw from the friendly base?
They took out one of the facility's structures. Commander, you need to draw those hostiles off our base.
Commander, we lose another building, this mission is over.
That's it, Commander. The enemy base has been destroyed.
Commander, we've completed all the primary objectives and you're clear to extract.
I'm on station to pick you up here whenever you're ready, boss.
As long as you're still in the AO, Commander, you'll need to keep the {TEAM_EMP.FactionDef.Demonym} base secure.
I'm not seeing any more hostiles in the area. Looks like a clean sweep, boss.
Move in to make the pickup, Meyer. Commander, your evac zone is here.
Heads up, commander, a lance of {TEAM_HOST.FactionDef.Demonym} units just entered the area. They're hostile to everyone!
We'll have to destroy that lance if we want to complete the mission.
Looks like our {TEAM_HOST.FactionDef.Demonym} friends have arrived. You'll need to get them shooting at the target facility.
Um, XO, are you sure about this? You see the size of those 'Mechs?!
Commander, I'm seeing hostile {TEAM_TAR_ALLY.FactionDef.Demonym} units in the area. Our target brought in allies for backup.
Our employer is saying we NEED to kill those units. Prepare to engage.
Commander, I'm seeing hostile {TEAM_TAR_ALLY.FactionDef.Demonym} units in the area. Our target brought in allies for backup.
If we decide to kill these units our employer if offering a bonus.
A lance of hostile {TEAM_TAR.FactionDef.Demonym} has landed nearby.
Our employer wants us to kill these guys. This mission isn't ending until they die.
A lance of hostile {TEAM_TAR.FactionDef.Demonym} has landed nearby.
Our employer is offering us some extra cash if we destroy these units too.
Scratch another target.
Good job, commander. All primary objectives complete. Get to evac, Sumire will pick you up here.
Leopard inbound, boss. Looks like more {TEAM_TAR.FactionDef.Demonym} units on the field.
As long as that facility is still standing, they're going to keep trying to defend it and secure that research data.
More {TEAM_TAR.FactionDef.Demonym} units, Commander. Just uh, just let me know if you need me to pull you out of there.
That's another {TEAM_TAR.FactionDef.Demonym} Leopard dropping off another lance, boss. Getting kinda messy down there.
Commander, more hostiles are entering the area. I've marked their LZ.
Commander, more hostiles are entering the area. I've marked their LZ.
Commander, we've got an enemy lance moving towards the {TEAM_EMP.FactionDef.Demonym} base.
Commander, we've got an enemy lance moving towards the {TEAM_EMP.FactionDef.Demonym} base.
Commander, {TEAM_TAR.FactionDef.Demonym} reinforcements are inbound to this location.
Commander, {TEAM_TAR.FactionDef.Demonym} reinforcements are inbound to this location.
Commander, {TEAM_TAR.FactionDef.Demonym} reinforcements are inbound to this location.
The {TEAM_EMP.FactionDef.Name} has provided some of their own forces to support us.
They're here to defend their base and will engage any hostiles that get too close.
Commander, the employer's base is under attack! Our {TEAM_EMP.FactionDef.Demonym} allies will stay close to the base to defend it.

longDescription: Commander, this mission is... insane. And I don't say that lightly. We're going to take a serious beating on this one.

shortDescription: Commander, we have a developing situation and need an unorthodox solution, which we're hoping your team can provide. Six hours ago, a heavily-armed {TEAM_TAR.FactionDef.Demonym} strike force landed near one of our research facilities and took control of it. That facility is stuffed with critical intelligence and research data, all of which is being accessed and transmitted off-planet right now. We simply don't have enough local firepower to dislodge them. We've got a plan, though. We're going to bait a third party into helping us destroy the base and its intel. You're the bait.
